core.controller.virtualrepresentations

Class VirtualRepresentation

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.controller.virtualrepresentations.VirtualRepresentation

  • public class VirtualRepresentation
extends Object
    This class provides all methods that are needed to manipulate virtual representations. It provides the usual getter and setter methods but also methods to aggregate and share data.
    Author:
    Jan-Peter.Schmidt

    • Constructor Detail

      • VirtualRepresentation

        protected VirtualRepresentation(String name,
                                VirtualRepresentation parent)
        Constructor for representations.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the representation. Name should only contain path of URI, not URI itself. E.g. /machine/sensor1 and not http://example.com/machine/sensor1
        parent - Representation that contains this representation. E.g. machines contains sensor1. Machine is parent of sensor1. Can be null.

      • setModelAsFile

        protected boolean setModelAsFile(File file)
        Method tries to create an model from delivered file and append it to this representation. Both dataaggregation and dataacquisition files can be uploaded that way. This method derives from filename suffix which one it is.
        Parameters:
        file - File to be stored in this representation. .rq files are stored as aggregation file anything else that can be parsed by Model.read() is stored as data acquisition file. See also
        Returns:
        true if file is valid and converted. False if file is corrupt.
        See Also:
        Model.read()

      • collectData

        public org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model collectData()
        This method reads the file dataAcquisition and collects data that are described in that file. These data are stored in a model and returned. Datacollection starts with transferring static data from acuqisition file. Afterwards SQL-Queries are executed and results converted to rdf and stored. If ODataSource is given the queries to that source will be executed and afterwards converted to RDF via RMLMapper.jar All relatives are stored to RDF Graph automatically.
        Returns:
        Model with all available data that are specified in data acquistion file.
